    comment: '<p>For styling a 7-column grid you may use something like :</p>\n<pre><code class="language-css">.column-1-7 {\n   width: 14.2857%;\n}\n.column-2-7 {\n   width: 28.5714%;\n}\n.column-3-7 {\n   width: 42.8571%;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Use the calc() function instead to make the maths behind the layout easier to understand :</p>\n<pre><code class="language-css">.column-1-7 {\n   width: calc(100% / 7);\n}\n.column-2-7 {\n   width: calc(100% / 7 * 2);\n}\n.column-3-7 {\n   width: calc(100% / 7 * 3);\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>You can also mix units!</p>\n<pre><code class="language-css">.mixing {\n   width: calc(50% + 30px);\n}\n</code></pre>\n',
